modules.description: Provides command line parsing and execution for Dream applications, translating configuration options into executable parameters. Accepts arguments such as port, host, and environment to customize server behavior. Enables direct server启动 from the terminal with specified runtime settings.

Provides functions to initialize and run a web application with command-line configuration, including interface, port, TLS settings, and custom commands. Works with types such as `Lwt.t`, `Dream.handler`, and `Cmdliner.Cmd.t` to manage asynchronous execution and CLI parsing. Used to start a Dream server with dynamic configuration via command-line flags or environment variables, enabling tailored deployment setups.
